The paper discusses the use of quasi-cyclic moderate-density parity-check (MDPC) codes in a McEliece-like cryptosystem, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also analyzes the error correction capability of the proposed ensembles, which involves coding theory (cs.CC) and complexity theory (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of density evolution and Monte Carlo simulations, which are common techniques in statistical inference (cs.SI).
